        <fr:title text="Matrix Multiply Unit (MXU)">Matrix Multiply Unit (MXU)</fr:title>
        <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter><html:p>A core component of the <fr:link href="/NZZ7/" title="TPU Architecture" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/NZZ7/" display-uri="NZZ7" type="local">TPU architecture</fr:link> responsible for performing matrix multiplication via a <html:em>systolic array</html:em>.</html:p><html:ul><html:li>256x256 totaling 65,536 <html:em>multiply accumulate</html:em> units i.e. each unit can multiply and add in one cycle.</html:li></html:ul>
 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);">Remark.</html:span> 
Can only do 256x256 matrix multiplication, so the order is 
<html:ol><html:li>Tiling the matrix to load from HBM to VMEM</html:li>
  <html:li>Compiler tiles from VMEM to 256x256 tiles to load into MXU.</html:li></html:ol>
</html:div>
<html:figure><html:img width="30%" src="/bafkrmickrnx5efnigkyxbpwks6lud2meikoqmsfy2llhy6lvb2y2bccpia.png" />
<html:figcaption>Note the input are offset so that the result from the first column can be accumulated int the second column. Can compute matmul in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2n - 1]]></fr:tex> cycles.</html:figcaption></html:figure></fr:mainmatter>
