            <fr:title text="ASIC accelerators">ASIC accelerators</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p><html:em>Application-Specific Integrated Circuits</html:em> fuse multiple operations into hardware that a general-purpose pipeline would have to schedule sequentially. The motivating intuition: if you frequently <html:em>multiply-accumulate</html:em>, the multiply and the add each traverse the entire pipeline separately. A dedicated multiply-accumulate ALU does both in one cycle.</html:p>
            <html:p>The cost-of-operation gap is large — 32-bit vs 8-bit addition has roughly an order of magnitude difference in energy per op. ASICs win by matching width to need.</html:p>
