                <fr:route>/2BGU/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Processing in Memory for ML">Processing in Memory for ML</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Notes on guest lecture by Yufeng Gu titled <html:em>Architecture and System Co-Design for Scalable Large Language Model Inference</html:em></html:p><html:p>TFLOPs increasing much faster than DRAM bandwidth -&gt; Hardware scaling is hitting the <html:em>memory wall</html:em>.</html:p><html:p>Data center power consumption also increasing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\approx ]]></fr:tex> 10% a year.</html:p><html:p><html:strong>GPUs are under low utilization for LLM inference</html:strong></html:p><html:ul><html:li>Prefix stage: parallel</html:li>
  <html:li>Decoding stage: sequential -&gt; bottleneck!</html:li></html:ul><html:p>As batch size increases, the <fr:link href="/TJLA/" title="KV-cache" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/TJLA/" display-uri="TJLA" type="local">KV-cache</fr:link> dominates memory usage.</html:p><html:ul><html:li>KV cache size grows with context length.</html:li>
  <html:li>Tradeoff between context length and batch size.</html:li></html:ul>
 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);">Remark.</html:span> 
Unlike fully-connected cannot batch self-attention because it depends on the individual prompts.
</html:div>
<html:p><html:strong style="font-family: var(--sans); font-weight: 500;">Recall.</html:strong> operational intensity is <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\text {compute throughput}}{\text {memory bandwidth}}]]></fr:tex></html:p><html:p><html:strong>Inference much lower operational intensity than GEMM!</html:strong></html:p><html:ul><html:li>Inference only doing matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\times ]]></fr:tex> row</html:li>
  <html:li>If embedding dim is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>, then this is only <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> ops / byte.</html:li></html:ul><html:p>Processing in memory (PIM) enables faster memory bandwidth.</html:p>
 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.85);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.06);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.85);">Problem.</html:span> Has lower memory capacity (fewer GB) due to added processing units (PU).
</html:div>

 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(40, 150, 80, 0.9);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(40, 150, 80, 0.06);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(40, 150, 80, 0.9);">Solution.</html:span> Use Compute eXpress Link (CXL) to do memory expansion to get high memory bandwidth + expend memory capacity.</html:div>

 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);">Remark.</html:span> 
Put high use operations i.e. vector multiplication, element-wise multiplication in PIM module (99% usage). Put more complicated operations on PNM accelerator. TODO: ISAs for each specified on slides (not available yet).
</html:div>

 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);">Remark.</html:span> 
CENT supports inter and intra-device communication via connecting communication controller to shared buffer and CXL port.
</html:div>
<html:p><html:strong style="font-family: var(--sans); font-weight: 500;">Communcation primitives.</html:strong> multicast and gather</html:p><html:ul><html:li>Multicast: send to all CXL devices.</html:li>
  <html:li>Gather: receive data sequentially from all CXL devices.</html:li>
  <html:li>Multicsat-gather -&gt; tensor parallel.</html:li></html:ul><html:p><html:em>Peer-to-peer:</html:em> can also support pipeline parallelism.</html:p>
 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);">Remark.</html:span> 
For fast communication, use tensor parallelism i.e. if connected via NVLink. If slower communication use pipeline parallelism. Can mix.
</html:div>

 <html:div class="jms-callout" style="
  margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
  padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
  border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);
  "><html:span style="font-weight: 600; color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);">Remark.</html:span> 
Longer context -&gt; better performance for PIM (TODO: why?). HBM + PIM does not scale. Cannot arbitrarily add PIM.
</html:div>
